# Week 15 - Day 7: Kahn’s Algorithm (Topological Sort - BFS)

## 📌 Problem Statement
Perform **Topological Sorting** of a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) using **Kahn’s Algorithm (BFS)**.

👉 Return a valid linear ordering of vertices such that:
For every directed edge `u → v`, `u` appears before `v`.

---

## 🚀 Approach (BFS - Kahn’s Algorithm)

This algorithm is based on **indegree (incoming edges)**.

---

## 🧠 Key Idea

1. Calculate indegree of all nodes  
2. Push nodes with indegree = 0 into queue  
3. While queue is not empty:
   - Pop node
   - Add to result
   - Reduce indegree of neighbors
   - If indegree becomes 0 → push into queue  

---
  #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Graph
{
    int V;
    list<int> *l;

public:
    Graph(int V)
    {
        this->V = V;
        l = new list<int>[V];
    }

    // Best practice: Add a destructor to free memory
    ~Graph()
    {
        delete[] l;
    }

    void addEdge(int u, int v)
    {
        l[u].push_back(v); // For directed graph, only add edge from u to v
    }

    void topoSort()
    {
        queue<int> q;
        vector<int> res;
        // kahn's algo
        // by indegree calculations
        vector<int> indegree(V, 0);
        for (int u = 0; u < V; u++)
        {
            for (int v : l[u])
            {
                indegree[v]++;
            }
        }

        // o indegree nodes were added in queue
        for (int u = 0; u < V; u++)
        {
            if (indegree[u] == 0)
            {
                q.push(u);
            }
        }

        // bfs
        while (q.size() > 0)
        {
            int curr = q.front();
            res.push_back(curr);
            q.pop();

            for (int v : l[curr])
            {
                indegree[v]--;
                if (indegree[v] == 0)
                {
                    q.push(v);
                }
            }
        }

        // printing
        for(int i=0;i<res.size();i++){
            cout<<res[i]<< " ";
        }
        cout<<endl;
    }
};

int main()
{

    Graph g(6);
    // asuming that graph was DAG(directed acyclic graph)
    g.addEdge(3, 1);
    g.addEdge(2, 3);
    g.addEdge(4, 0);
    g.addEdge(4, 1);
    g.addEdge(5, 0);
    g.addEdge(5, 2);

    g.topoSort();

    return 0;
}

